RRBS vs. 850k data¶

  • see also http://mhanna.web.elte.hu/rrbs/MarkerRegions.html and http://mhanna.web.elte.hu/rrbs/checkPromoters.html for RRBS results
  • 850k top differentially methylated probes and marker gene regions: https://icsabai.github.io/hidden/methyl850k.html , data tables: https://kooplex-fiek.elte.hu/seafile/f/d36357398bd74667a935/

Conclusion¶

  • only very low portion of 850k probes are present in the RRBS data, typically 3000-13000 probes in samples
  • there are only 461 bead array positions, that are present in all 10 RRBS samples
  • the correlation between bead array beta and RRBS methylation ratio values is around 0.8
  • there are many saturated (0 or 1) RRBS values

print('These are the pairs for samples where we have both RRBS and 850k:')
nat = []
adcrc = []
natSample = []
adcrcSample = []

for i in range(5):   # there are 12 pairs total, but here we use only the old samples with RRBS
    e1 = sampleCrossId['DIAGENODE ID'].values[2*i]
    e2 = sampleCrossId['DIAGENODE ID'].values[2*i+1]
    b1 = sampleAnnot[sampleAnnot['SampleID']==e1]['ChipID'].values[0]
    b2 = sampleAnnot[sampleAnnot['SampleID']==e2]['ChipID'].values[0]
    if i==3: # for some resaon here they are in the other orders
        nat.append(b2)
        adcrc.append(b1)
        natSample.append(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i+1])
        adcrcSample.append(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i])
        print(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i+1],sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i],
         e2,e1,b2,b1)
    else:
        nat.append(b1)
        adcrc.append(b2)
        natSample.append(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i])
        adcrcSample.append(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i+1])
        print(sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i],sampleCrossId['Sample ID'].values[2*i+1],
         e1,e2,b1,b2)

allMerge = []
for x in np.concatenate([natSample,adcrcSample]):
    fnam = dataRootRRBS + x + '_trimmed_bismark_bt2.bismark.cov'
    print(fnam)
    rrbs = pd.read_csv(fnam,sep='\t',header=None, names=['chrom', 'posStart', 'posEnd', 'methRatio100', 'methCnt', 'unMethCnt'])
    merge1 = pd.merge(df2[['IlmnID',  'CHR', 'MAPINFO',x]],rrbs,left_on=['CHR', 'MAPINFO'],right_on=['chrom','posStart'])
    allMerge.append([x,merge1.copy()])

4. Calculate correlations and plot¶

In [21]:
for i,x in enumerate(np.concatenate([natSample,adcrcSample])):
    hits = allMerge[i][1].shape[0]
    corr = np.corrcoef(allMerge[i][1][x].values.astype(float),y=allMerge[i][1]['methRatio100'].values/100)[0,1]
    plt.figure(figsize=[8,8])
    plt.plot(allMerge[i][1][x].values,allMerge[i][1]['methRatio100'].values/100,'.', alpha=0.5)
    plt.plot([0,1],[0,1],'-')
    plt.title(x + ':' + str(hits) + ' positions matched. Corr='+str(corr) )
    plt.xlabel('850k bead array beta')
    plt.ylabel('RRBS meth prob')
    plt.grid()
    plt.show()
